#. type: Content of: <sect1><title>
#: clfs-en/BOOK/system-config/common/locale.xml:9
msgid "Setting Up Locale Information"
msgstr "Configuration des informations pour la locale"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><indexterm><primary>
#: clfs-en/BOOK/system-config/common/locale.xml:13
msgid "/etc/locale.conf"
msgstr "/etc/locale.conf"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: clfs-en/BOOK/system-config/common/locale.xml:16
msgid ""
"The <filename>/etc/locale.conf</filename> below sets some environment "
"variables necessary for native language support. Setting them properly "
"results in:"
msgstr ""
"Le fichier <filename>/etc/locale.conf</filename> ci-dessous définit "
"certaines variables d'environnement nécessaires au support de la langue. En "
"les réglant correctement, on obtient que&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: clfs-en/BOOK/system-config/common/locale.xml:22
msgid "The output of programs translated into the native language"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: clfs-en/BOOK/system-config/common/locale.xml:25
msgid ""
"Correct classification of characters into letters, digits and other classes."
" This is necessary for <command>bash</command> to properly accept non-ASCII "
"characters in command lines in non-English locales"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: clfs-en/BOOK/system-config/common/locale.xml:30
msgid "The correct alphabetical sorting order for the country"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: clfs-en/BOOK/system-config/common/locale.xml:33
msgid "Appropriate default paper size"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: clfs-en/BOOK/system-config/common/locale.xml:36
msgid "Correct formatting of monetary, time, and date values"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: clfs-en/BOOK/system-config/common/locale.xml:40
msgid ""
"Replace <replaceable>[ll]</replaceable> below with the two-letter code for "
"the desired language (e.g., <quote>en</quote>) and "
"<replaceable>[CC]</replaceable> with the two-letter code for the appropriate"
" country (e.g., <quote>GB</quote> or <quote>US</quote>).  "
"<replaceable>[charmap]</replaceable> should be replaced with the canonical "
"charmap for your chosen locale. Optional modifiers such as "
"<quote>@euro</quote> may also be present."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: clfs-en/BOOK/system-config/common/locale.xml:48
msgid ""
"The list of all locales supported by Glibc can be obtained by running the "
"following command:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><screen>
#: clfs-en/BOOK/system-config/common/locale.xml:51
#, no-wrap
msgid "<userinput>locale -a</userinput>"
msgstr "<userinput>locale -a</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: clfs-en/BOOK/system-config/common/locale.xml:53
msgid ""
"Locales can have a number of synonyms, e.g. <quote>ISO-8859-1</quote> is "
"also referred to as <quote>iso8859-1</quote> and <quote>iso88591</quote>.  "
"Some applications cannot handle the various synonyms correctly, so it is "
"safest to choose the canonical name for a particular locale. To determine "
"the canonical name, run the following command, where <replaceable>[locale "
"name]</replaceable> is the output given by <command>locale -a</command> for "
"your preferred locale (<quote>en_US.utf8</quote> in our example)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><screen>
#: clfs-en/BOOK/system-config/common/locale.xml:61
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<userinput>LC_ALL=<replaceable>[locale name]</replaceable> locale "
"charmap</userinput>"
msgstr ""
"<userinput>LC_ALL=<replaceable>[locale name]</replaceable> locale "
"charmap</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: clfs-en/BOOK/system-config/common/locale.xml:63
msgid ""
"For the <quote>en_US.utf8</quote> locale, the above command will print:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><screen>
#: clfs-en/BOOK/system-config/common/locale.xml:66
#, no-wrap
msgid "<computeroutput>UTF-8</computeroutput>"
msgstr "<computeroutput>UTF-8</computeroutput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: clfs-en/BOOK/system-config/common/locale.xml:68
msgid ""
"This results in a final locale setting of <quote>en_US.UTF-8</quote>.  It is"
" important that the locale found using the heuristic above is tested prior "
"to it being added to <filename>/etc/locale.conf</filename>:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><screen>
#: clfs-en/BOOK/system-config/common/locale.xml:72
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<userinput>LC_ALL=[locale name] locale territory\n"
"LC_ALL=[locale name] locale language\n"
"LC_ALL=[locale name] locale charmap\n"
"LC_ALL=[locale name] locale int_curr_symbol\n"
"LC_ALL=[locale name] locale int_prefix</userinput>"
msgstr ""
"<userinput>LC_ALL=[locale name] locale territory\n"
"LC_ALL=[locale name] locale language\n"
"LC_ALL=[locale name] locale charmap\n"
"LC_ALL=[locale name] locale int_curr_symbol\n"
"LC_ALL=[locale name] locale int_prefix</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: clfs-en/BOOK/system-config/common/locale.xml:78
msgid ""
"The above commands should print the language name, the character encoding "
"used by the locale, the local currency, and the prefix to dial before the "
"telephone number in order to get into the country. If any of the commands "
"above fail with a message similar to the one shown below, this means that "
"your locale was either not installed in Chapter 10 or is not supported by "
"the default installation of Glibc."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><screen>
#: clfs-en/BOOK/system-config/common/locale.xml:85
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<computeroutput>locale: Cannot set LC_* to default locale: No such file or "
"directory</computeroutput>"
msgstr ""
"<computeroutput>locale: Cannot set LC_* to default locale: No such file or "
"directory</computeroutput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: clfs-en/BOOK/system-config/common/locale.xml:87
msgid ""
"If this happens, you should either install the desired locale using the "
"<command>localedef</command> command, or consider choosing a different "
"locale. Further instructions assume that there are no such error messages "
"from Glibc."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: clfs-en/BOOK/system-config/common/locale.xml:92
msgid ""
"Some packages beyond CLFS may also lack support for your chosen locale.  One"
" example is the X library (part of the X Window System), which outputs the "
"following error message:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><screen>
#: clfs-en/BOOK/system-config/common/locale.xml:96
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<computeroutput>Warning: locale not supported by Xlib, locale set to "
"C</computeroutput>"
msgstr ""
"<computeroutput>Warning: locale not supported by Xlib, locale set to "
"C</computeroutput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: clfs-en/BOOK/system-config/common/locale.xml:98
msgid ""
"Sometimes it is possible to fix this by removing the charmap part of the "
"locale specification, as long as that does not change the character map that"
" Glibc associates with the locale (this can be checked by running the "
"<command>locale charmap</command> command in both locales). For example, one"
" would have to change &quot;de_DE.ISO-8859-15@euro&quot; to "
"&quot;de_DE@euro&quot; in order to get this locale recognized by Xlib."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: clfs-en/BOOK/system-config/common/locale.xml:105
msgid ""
"Other packages can also function incorrectly (but may not necessarily "
"display any error messages) if the locale name does not meet their "
"expectations. In those cases, investigating how other Linux distributions "
"support your locale might provide some useful information."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: clfs-en/BOOK/system-config/common/locale.xml:110
msgid ""
"Once the proper locale settings have been determined, create the "
"<filename>/etc/locale.conf</filename> file:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><screen>
#: clfs-en/BOOK/system-config/common/locale.xml:113
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<userinput>cat &gt; /etc/locale.conf &lt;&lt; \"EOF\"\n"
"<literal># Begin /etc/locale.conf\n"
"\n"
"LANG=<replaceable>[ll]</replaceable>_<replaceable>[CC]</replaceable>.<replaceable>[charmap]</replaceable><replaceable>[@modifiers]</replaceable>\n"
"\n"
"# End /etc/locale.conf</literal>\n"
"EOF</userinput>"
msgstr ""
"<userinput>cat &gt; /etc/locale.conf &lt;&lt; \"EOF\"\n"
"<literal># Begin /etc/locale.conf\n"
"\n"
"LANG=<replaceable>[ll]</replaceable>_<replaceable>[CC]</replaceable>.<replaceable>[charmap]</replaceable><replaceable>[@modifiers]</replaceable>\n"
"\n"
"# End /etc/locale.conf</literal>\n"
"EOF</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: clfs-en/BOOK/system-config/common/locale.xml:121
msgid ""
"Note that you can modify <filename>/etc/locale.conf</filename> with "
"systemd's <command>localectl</command> utility. To use "
"<command>localectl</command> for the example above, run:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><screen>
#: clfs-en/BOOK/system-config/common/locale.xml:125
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<userinput>localectl set-locale "
"LANG=\"<replaceable>[ll]_[CC][charmap][@modifiers]</replaceable>\"</userinput>"
msgstr ""
"<userinput>localectl set-locale "
"LANG=\"<replaceable>[ll]_[CC][charmap][@modifiers]</replaceable>\"</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: clfs-en/BOOK/system-config/common/locale.xml:127
msgid ""
"You can also specify other language specific environment variables such as "
"<envar>LANG</envar>, <envar>LC_CTYPE</envar>, <envar>LC_NUMERIC</envar> or "
"any other environment variable from <command>locale</command> output. Just "
"separate them with a space. An example where <envar>LANG</envar> is set as "
"en_US.UTF-8 but <envar>LC_CTYPE</envar> is set as just en_US is:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><screen>
#: clfs-en/BOOK/system-config/common/locale.xml:133
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<userinput>localectl set-locale LANG=\"en_US.UTF-8\" "
"LC_CTYPE=\"en_US\"</userinput>"
msgstr ""
"<userinput>localectl set-locale LANG=\"en_US.UTF-8\" "
"LC_CTYPE=\"en_US\"</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><note><para>
#: clfs-en/BOOK/system-config/common/locale.xml:135
msgid ""
"Please note that <command>localectl</command> command can be used only on a "
"system booted with systemd."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: clfs-en/BOOK/system-config/common/locale.xml:137
msgid ""
"Setting the keyboard layout, screen font, and locale-related environment "
"variables are the only internationalization steps needed to support locales "
"that use ordinary single-byte encodings and left-to-right writing direction."
" UTF-8 has been tested on the English, French, German, Italian, and Spanish "
"locales. All other locales are untested. If you discover issues with any "
"other locale please open a ticket in our Trac system."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><para>
#: clfs-en/BOOK/system-config/common/locale.xml:144
msgid ""
"Some locales need additional programs and support. CLFS will not be "
"supporting these locales in the book. We welcome the support for these other"
" locales via <ulink url=\"&cblfs-root;\"/>."
msgstr ""
